<subSubSection id="C31E6558FFD871678D98FC4E7D2C7CFB" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBB36D3FFD871668D98FC4E7FCF7EDC" blockId="2.[136,1452,914,2093]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
In accordance with the rules outlined by Miller in the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668E25FC4F7DAA7F0C" box="[768,907,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Introduction</emphasis>
to the eighth edition of the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668995FC4F7B857F0C" box="[1200,1444,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Gardeners Dictionary</emphasis>
, the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668C7BFB937CE27F28" authority="Miller (1768" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[350,707,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668C7BFB937C007F28" box="[350,545,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Santolina villosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD871668F09FB937CE27F28" author="Miller, P." box="[556,707,1058,1084]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" refId="ref4284" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The Gardeners Dictionary, 8 th ed. Printed for the author, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 541" type="book" year="1768">Miller (1768</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668FF6FB937D557F29" authority="No." authorityName="No." box="[723,884,1058,1085]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668FF6FB937D1F7F28" box="[723,830,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Santolina</emphasis>
No.
</taxonomicName>
2) includes a Latin diagnosis “2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668828FB937B8A7F28" box="[1293,1451,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">SANTOLINA</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668DB4FBF77EFF7F74" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[145,222,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668DB4FBF77EFF7F74" box="[145,222,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) pedunculis unifloris, calycibus globosis, foliis quadrisariàm dentatis tomentosis” and its English translation “ 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668DB1FBDB7EE17FBC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Lavender-cotton with one flower upon a foot-stalk, globular empalements, and woolly leaves which are indented four ways</emphasis>
”, followed by the synonym “ 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668F30FB3F7A0C7FBC" box="[533,1069,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668F30FB3F7D367FBC" box="[533,791,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="flore" subSpecies="majore">Santolina flore majore</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668E01FB3F7D7D7FBC" box="[804,860,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliis">foliis</taxonomicName>
villosis &amp; incanis
</emphasis>
. Tourn, Inst. 460” (this reference being to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD871668DCDFB037FF67FD9" author="Tournefort, J." box="[232,471,1202,1229]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" refId="ref4801" refString="Tournefort, J. (1719) Institutiones rei herbariae. Editio tertia. E Typographia Regia, Parisiis, 695 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 153569" type="book" year="1719">Tournefort 1719: 460</bibRefCitation>
) translated into English as “Lavender-cotton with a larger flower and hoary leaves”. The protologue is also accompanied by a more detailed description in the main article on the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668983FB677B307FE4" box="[1190,1297,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668983FB677B307FE4" box="[1190,1297,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Santolina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: “The second sort has a shrubby stalk with branches out like the former [i.e. No. 1 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668EB2FB4A7AA07E00" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[919,1153,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chamaecyparissus">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668EB2FB4A7AA07E00" box="[919,1153,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">S. chamaecyparissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.], but the plants seldom grow so tall. The branches are divided into a great number of stalks, which are short, hoary, and garnished very closely below with leaves shaped like thofe of the other sort, but are shorter, thicker, and whiter; the flowers are much larger, and the brims of the florets are more reflexed; they are of a deeper sulphur colour than the other, but appear at the same time”. Miller concludes his description by providing information about the origin of this species, which according to him “grows naturally in 
<collectingCountry id="F3137643FFD871668CBFFA1F7FC17EDC" box="[410,480,1454,1480]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Spain</collectingCountry>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36D3FFD871668D98FA627FEA7C24" blockId="2.[136,1452,914,2093]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
No particular specimens or illustrations are cited in the protologue, so the 
<typeStatus id="54BF8871FFD871668923FA637A4C7EF8" box="[1030,1133,1490,1516]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">lectotype</typeStatus>
has to be selected from any elements of the original material that were available to Miller before the eighth edition of the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668996FA477B8A7D04" box="[1203,1451,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Gardeners Dictionary</emphasis>
was published in 1768. Miller’s own personal herbarium, said to contain almost 10,000 specimens, was purchased by Sir Joseph Banks in 1774 and was later incorporated into the General Herbarium at BM (Britten 1913). Unfortunately, no specimen identifiable as 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668CE5F9D27C067D68" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[448,551,1634,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668CE5F9D27C067D68" box="[448,551,1634,1661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">S. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can now be found in Miller’s own collection at BM. There is also no material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668DADF9367ECF7DB4" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[136,238,1670,1697]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668DADF9367ECF7DB4" box="[136,238,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">S. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
amongst the specimens of plants grown at the Chelsea Physic Garden (of which Miller was the director from 1722 to 1771) and sent to the Royal Society between 1722 and 1796 as part of an agreement between Sir Hans Sloane and the Worshipful Society of Apothecaries. This collection of nearly 4,000 specimens gathered by Miller’s assistants (not by Miller himself) was transferred to the British Museum in 1781 and integrated into the General Herbarium in the late 1880s (
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD871668C17F8A77F9F7C24" author="Stearn, W. T." box="[306,446,1814,1840]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" pagination="293 - 307" refId="ref4658" refString="Stearn, W. T. (1972) Philip Miller and the Plants from the Chelsea Physic Garden presented to the Royal Society of London, 1723 - 1796. Transactions of the Botanical Society of Edinburgh 41 (3): 293 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03746607208685233" type="journal article" year="1972">Stearn 1972</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36D3FFD871678D98F88B7A087A30" blockId="2.[136,1452,914,2093]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,293]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="236" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
One specimen however, directly corresponding to Miller’s concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668EE7F88B7A5C7C40" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[962,1149,1850,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668EE7F88B7A5C7C40" box="[962,1149,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Santolina villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, still survives in the Sloane Herbarium (BM-SL) at the Natural History Museum in London (
<figureCitation id="133F2A56FFD871668E73F8EF7DBB7C6C" box="[854,922,1886,1912]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,190,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[207,1381,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype of Santolina villosa Miller (BM-SL: H.S. 294 fol. 65 – specimen on the left hand side of the folio). Photography by courtesy of Herbarium BM; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426176/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). It forms part of a consignment of nearly 1,500 specimens of various plants grown by Miller at the Chelsea Physic Garden and presented to Sir Hans Sloane between 1727 and 1739 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD871668C18F8177FE47CD4" author="Wajer, J." box="[317,453,1958,1984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" pagination="72 - 77" refId="ref4999" refString="Wajer, J. (2020) Philip Miller. In: Carine, M. (Ed.) The Collectors: Creating Hans Sloane's extraordinary herbarium. Natural History Museum, London, pp. 72 - 77." type="book chapter" year="2020">Wajer 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen can be found on folio 
<quantity id="4CFC9B36FFD871668E57F8177D8A7CD4" box="[882,939,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6509999999999998" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="65.0">65 in</quantity>
Volume No. 294 of Sloane’s Collection (H.S. 294 fol. 65), where it is mounted together with the specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668E4FF87A7A747CF0" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[874,1109,1994,2021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chamaecyparissus">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668E4FF87A7A747CF0" box="[874,1109,1994,2021]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">S. chamaecyparissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(probably for comparison). It consists of a branch with leaves and capitula identified by Miller as “ 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD871668EBBF85F7F0A7338" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668EBBF85F7ABD731C" box="[926,1180,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="flore" subSpecies="majore">Santolina flore majore</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD871668981F85F7AFD731C" box="[1188,1244,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliis">foliis</taxonomicName>
villosis &amp; incanis Inst. R. H. 460
</emphasis>
”, which is the Tournefort’s name (1719: 460) cited in the protologue for 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD87166897EF7A27AE37338" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[1115,1218,2066,2093]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD87166897EF7A27AE37338" box="[1115,1218,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="235">S. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was indeed under this very name that Miller initially described this species in the first edition of the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678937FF2F7B267BAC" box="[1042,1287,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Gardeners Dictionary</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD971678830FF2F7BBE7BAC" author="Miller, P." box="[1301,1439,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" refId="ref4217" refString="Miller, P. (1731) The Gardeners Dictionary, 1 st ed. Printed for the autor, London." type="book" year="1731">Miller 1731</bibRefCitation>
). Miller continued using Tournefort’s polynomial solely until the seventh edition of the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678962FF727AE17BC8" box="[1095,1216,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Dictionary</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD9716789EAFF737B777BC9" author="Miller, P." box="[1231,1366,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" refId="ref4239" refString="Miller, P. (1756 - 59) The Gardeners Dictionary, 7 th ed. Printed for the autor, London. [https: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 96668 j]" type="url" year="1756">Miller 1756</bibRefCitation>
–1759), when he added to it a new Latin diagnosis and a much longer English description, all reproduced verbatim in the eighth edition of the 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678C01FEBA7FBC7A30" box="[292,413,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Dictionary</emphasis>
in 1768, where the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD971678FE5FEBA7D067A30" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[704,807,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678FE5FEBA7D067A30" box="[704,807,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">S. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was validly published.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7B665BFFD971678DADF9257B407DBE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426174" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5426174" box="[136,1377,1684,1706]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426174/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" startId="3.[136,229,1684,1706]" targetBox="[379,1236,314,1655]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BBB36D3FFD971678DADF9257B407DBE" blockId="3.[136,1377,1684,1706]" box="[136,1377,1684,1706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678DADF9257EDF7DBD" bold="true" box="[136,254,1684,1706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD971678CA6F9257C527DBE" authority="Poir." authorityName="Poir." box="[387,627,1684,1706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ericoides">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678CA6F9257C1C7DBD" box="[387,573,1684,1705]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Santolina ericoides</emphasis>
Poir.
</taxonomicName>
, illustration “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD971678FD0F9257A657DBD" authority=", Dodonaei" authorityName="Dodonaei" box="[757,1092,1684,1705]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Abrotonum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foemina">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678FD0F9257DF87DBD" box="[757,985,1684,1705]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">ABROTONUM foemina</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678EC0F9257A657DBD" box="[997,1092,1684,1705]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Dodonaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD971678948F9257B7C7DBE" author="Dalechamps, J." box="[1133,1373,1684,1706]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" refId="ref3719" refString="Dalechamps, J. (1586) Historia generalis plantarvm, [Pars prima]. Apud Gvlielmvm Rovillivm, Lugduni, 1095 pp. [https: // archive. org / details / bub _ gb __ NGRilRpGGIC / page / n 949 / mode / 2 up]" type="book" year="1586">Daléchamps (1586: 938)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBB36D3FFD971678D98F9697D2C7CFB" blockId="3.[136,1452,1752,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">
<materialsCitation id="3B6C3C8EFFD971678D98F9697D287CFB" country="Spain" county="At" location="The" municipality="Central-Eastern" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678D98F9697EC87DE6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678D98F9697EC87DE6" box="[189,233,1752,1778]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="The" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">The</location>
specimen in the 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678C80F9697CA27DE6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678C80F9697CA27DE6" box="[421,643,1752,1778]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Sloane's Herbarium" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Sloane’s Herbarium</location>
is the only surviving element of the original material for 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D50FFD971678825F9687B467DE6" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" box="[1280,1383,1752,1779]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Santolina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678825F9687B467DE6" box="[1280,1383,1752,1779]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">S. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it matches the current concept and use of 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678F1BF94D7CB97C02" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678F1BF94D7CB97C02" box="[574,664,1788,1814]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Miller's" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Miller’s</location>
name (
<bibRefCitation id="EF954B22FFD971678FCDF94D7D8C7C02" author="Giaco, A. &amp; Astuti, G. &amp; Peruzzi, L." box="[744,941,1788,1814]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" pagination="189 - 201" refId="ref3810" refString="Giaco, A., Astuti, G. &amp; Peruzzi, L. (2021) Typification and nomenclature of the names in the Santolina chamaecyparissus species complex (Asteraceae). Taxon 70 (1): 189 - 201. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12429" type="journal article" year="2021">
Giacò 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678E16F94C7D4A7C02" box="[819,875,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
), showing several of the diagnostic characters for this taxon (e.g. whitish or greyish tomentose leaves and stems and hairy involucral bracts) (
<figureCitation id="133F2A56FFD9716789FDF8917B3E7C2E" box="[1240,1311,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1196,1218]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,317,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-69@5.[231,1357,317,1172]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Detail of the bracts, leaves, and stem of the specimen of Santolina villosa Mill. preserved in the Sloane Herbarium (BM-SL: H.S. 294 fol. 65 [specimen on the left hand side of the folio]) at BM-SL. Photography by courtesy of Herbarium BM; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426178/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678810F8917B8A7C2E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678810F8917B8A7C2E" box="[1333,1451,1824,1850]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="According" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">According</location>
to 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678D83F8F57EC87C4A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678D83F8F57EC87C4A" box="[166,233,1860,1886]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Giaco" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Giacò</location>
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678DD7F8F47F0A7C4A" box="[242,299,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
(in revision), this species shows two different cytotypes. 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678E99F8F57A2A7C4A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678E99F8F57A2A7C4A" box="[956,1035,1860,1886]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Indeed" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Indeed</location>
, material from 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD97167899EF8F57B017C4A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD97167899EF8F57B017C4A" box="[1211,1312,1860,1886]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Southern" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Southern</location>
<collectingCountry id="F3137643FFD97167880DF8F57B497C4A" box="[1320,1384,1860,1886]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Spain</collectingCountry>
(Gor, Granada) is hexaploid (2 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678CBAF8D87F8C7C96" box="[415,429,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">n</emphasis>
= 6 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678CFFF8D87FC77C96" box="[474,486,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">x</emphasis>
= 54), while material from 
<location id="8EDB6008FFD971678E05F8D97D537C96" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03AD87C5FFD871678DADFCFB7D2C7CFB:8EDB6008FFD971678E05F8D97D537C96" box="[800,882,1896,1922]" country="Spain" county="At" municipality="Central-Eastern" name="Central" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Central</location>
and 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BDFACA9FFD971678E8FF8D97A7B7C96" box="[938,1114,1896,1922]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Central-Eastern</collectingMunicipality>
<collectingCountry id="F3137643FFD971678944F8D97A807C96" box="[1121,1185,1896,1922]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Spain</collectingCountry>
is tetraploid (2 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD971678868F8D87B7A7C96" box="[1357,1371,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">n</emphasis>
= 2 
<emphasis id="B970EAC1FFD9716788ADF8D87BB57C96" box="[1416,1428,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">x</emphasis>
= 36). 
<collectingCounty id="62DA4E5FFFD971678D9EF83C7EF67CB3" box="[187,215,1933,1959]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">At</collectingCounty>
the present state of knowledge, there is no obvious morphological feature distinguishing these cytotypes, so that it is not possible to infer to which cytotype the 
<typeStatus id="54BF8871FFD971678F99F8017D027CDE" box="[700,803,1968,1994]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">lectotype</typeStatus>
may apply. However, more studies are needed to elucidate the systematic relationships between these two cytotypes
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
